{"lemma":"فَضَلاتٌ","slug":"فَضَلاتٌ","root":"ف.ض.ل","root_slug":"ف-ض-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ض-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34075","n34082","n34083"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what remains, residue, remainder"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feces"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a word that is used in addition to words normally used"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun from فَضَلَ (faḍala, “to be left over”)."},"ipa":["/fadˤ.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34075","headword_ar":"فضّلهُ","root":"fDl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY gayorihi","text_ar":"عَلَى غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafoDiylN","text_ar":"تَفْضِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maz~aAhu","text_ar":"مَزَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed to him an excellence distinguishing him from"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faD~alotuhu EalaY","text_ar":"فَضَّلْتُهُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayorihi","text_ar":"غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I judged him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, * TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be more excellent than another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * Msb, TA: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made him"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, * TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * Msb, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wafaD~alonaAhumo EalaY","text_ar":"وَفَضَّلْنَاهُمْ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyrK mim~ano xalaqonaA","text_ar":"كَثِيرٍ مِمَّنْ خَلَقْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xvii. 72, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have made them to excel many of those that we have created"},{"kind":"text","text":"], has been expl. as meaning that the excellence of the son of Adam consists in his walking erect, whereas the beasts, the camels and the asses and the like, walk pronely; and the son of Adam takes food with his hands, whereas the other animals take it with the mouth. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@ll~`hu faD~ala baEoDakumo EalaY baEoDK","text_ar":"وَا@للّٰهُ فَضَّلَ بَعْضَكُمْ عَلَى بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xvi. 73, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And God hath made some of you to excel some"},{"kind":"text","text":"others], means, in ability, and wealth, and rank or station, and power; which are excellences that may be acquired. (Er-Rághib, TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fD~lhu bihi","text_ar":"فضّلهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaS~ahu","text_ar":"خَصَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He distinguished him particularly, peculiarly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"specially, by it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a thing]. (A and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xS","text_ar":"خص"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fD~l fiY AlEaTaA='i","text_ar":"فضّل فِى العَطَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave to some more than to others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afq","text_ar":"افق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  [An explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fD~l","text_ar":"فضّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"given by Golius, as on the authority of the K, (“ i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wsx","text_ar":"وسخ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sordibus infecit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"vel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pro sordida habuit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"quotidianam vestem, ”) is a strange mistake; app. caused by his finding in a copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~afoDiylu Alt~awosiyxu","text_ar":"التَّفْضِيلُ التَّوْسِيخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~afaD~ulu Alt~awa$~uHu","text_ar":"التَّفَضُّلُ التَّوَشُّحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 5. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisomu Alt~afoDiyli","text_ar":"اِسْمُ التَّفْضِيلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The noun of the attribution of excess"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellence"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a term applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the comparative and superlative noun"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"epithet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu Alt~afoDiyli","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ التَّفْضِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it is regularly of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see exs. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34082","headword_ar":"فَضْلَةٌ","root":"fDl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", former half, in two places. ―         -b2-  [Hence, as used by grammarians,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dispensable member of a proposition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as the objective complement of a verb, when the suppression thereof is not detrimental [to the meaning];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumodapN","text_ar":"عُمْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (I'Ak, p. 143) [The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDalaAtN","text_ar":"فَضَلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clothes that are used for sleeping"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) [so called] because they are an addition over and above the clothes that are used on various [other] occasions. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiDaAlN","text_ar":"فِضَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see also in what here follows]: (O, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaDolapu","text_ar":"الفَضْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned by A'Obeyd as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a name for wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or it signifies, accord. to AHn,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wine that alters"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become altered"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in colour after oldness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ISd says that it is so called because the choice, or best, or most excellent, part thereof [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA^n~","text_ar":"لانّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HmymhA","text_ar":"حميمها"},{"kind":"text","text":"in my original (an obvious mistranscription) I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^an~a SamiymahaA","text_ar":"لِاَنَّ صَمِيمَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is what remains: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDalaAtN","text_ar":"فَضَلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiDaAlN","text_ar":"فِضَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the latter word mentioned above as a syn. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolapN","text_ar":"فَضْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n34083","headword_ar":"فِضْلَةٌ","root":"fDl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is a n. of the same kind as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilosapN","text_ar":"جِلْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rikobapN","text_ar":"رِكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, S, O, TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasanu","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfiDolapi","text_ar":"الفِضْلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is comely in respect of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the manner of wearing a single garment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * K, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","S","O","TA"]}]}}